title: Materials Science, Computer and Information Technology
description:
Materials Science, Computer and Information Technology (Trans Tech, 2014).pdf

More than 1,200 papers cover advanced materials science, chemical engineering and processing technologies; applied mechanics, construction, and testing technologies; biological and medical research; resource, energy, and electronic development and environmental engineering; advanced technologies in modeling, simulation, and optimization; computation methods and algorithms and intelligent engineering applications; advanced technologies in mechanical engineering, mechatronics, automation, measurements, control, and manufacturing technology; communication, signal and image processing, and data acquisition and recognition technologies; general principles of information technology, web and networks engineering, information security, electronic engineering, and software application and development; and advanced information and innovation technologies for management, logistics, economics, education, and assessment
